I asked for soup and they served me cold soup. When I returned to the store they apologized and told me that they would warm up another bowl of soup. When they gave me that bowl of soup it was lukewarm and to to make matters worst it was not fresh. The soup tasted like something that might have been cooked if not a few days prior. As if they might have had the soup in the freezer and removed it to be warmed and served. The dumplings were soggy, the other stuff in it was disgusting. I had to throw it out. How do serve the public food that was cooked days ago. The audacity. This was so disappointing. Shame on them. I have had friends who have had bad experiences as well. You cannot serve the public food that was prepared and stored in the freezer or refrigerator from days ago. Most of us know the difference when the food isn't fresh. Shame shame shame.

This location is hit or miss in terms of customer service. The misses being more frequent. They are rude, dismissive, and generally unpleasant. A lot of it seems to be a management issue in their defense. They always run off things and seem overwhelmed by the number of customers. I like the food there but it makes the trip there a cringe-worthy proposition that I would rather avoid. As a final note -- if you are a fan do drop by you won't be disappointed by the food. Just bring a thick skin. All others look elsewhere for Jamaican food and don't let this location put you off.

HORRIBLE CUSTOMER SERVICE! There is one manager that is very nice, actually 2 (both men). Also one or 2 cashiers. But for the most part, they are very nasty for no reason at all! The soup is NEVER ready on time! I have to double check that I have utensils & napkins. They really need a staff overhaul at this location. The food, for the most part is delicious. More registers are necessary to handle the lunch time crowd. And the staff REALLY needs an attitude adjustment. They whisper amongst each other about the customers. Sometimes, they even PURPOSELY skip customers that they do not like. I have noticed a drop in customers lately & if this keeps up, they will continue to lose business!!
